<section id="command-setfocus">
<title>SETFOCUS</title>
<indexterm><primary>SETFOCUS</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>SETFOCUS</command> <parameter>caption</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Selects a window whose caption (or title) is <parameter>caption</parameter>.
When a window has focus, it is selected and all keyboard input is directed to it.
</para>

<para>
A window's "caption" is not the same as the window's "name" used by the <link linkend="windows-commands">windows commands</link>.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>


<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SETFOCUS [&PRODUCTNAME;]</userinput>
</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>See Also</term>
<listitem><simplelist>
<member><link linkend="command-getfocus">GETFOCUS</link></member>
</simplelist></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
